{"kind":"article","hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents"]]},"sections":[],"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/Layouts","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"primaryContentSections":[{"content":[{"type":"heading","level":2,"anchor":"Overview","text":"Overview"},{"type":"heading","level":3,"anchor":"Colored-Surface","text":"Colored Surface"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Colored backgrounds use surface colors to maximize the contrast with content.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"The colors of several OUDS components (for instance ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSButton","type":"reference"},{"text":" or ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSLink","type":"reference"},{"text":") are automatically adjusted if they are placed on ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSColoredSurface","type":"reference"},{"text":".","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"To do so, some tokens associated with these specific colors can be customized and are identified with the ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Mono","type":"text"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"text":" suffix (for instance ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"buttonColorBgDefaultEnabledMono","type":"text"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"text":" of ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"OrangeThemeButtonComponentTokensProvider"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"text":").","type":"text"}]},{"level":4,"type":"heading","text":"How it works","anchor":"How-it-works"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"According to the color, the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"OUDSColoredSurface"},{"type":"text","text":" component adds in SwiftUI environment two flags:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"oudsUseMonochrome"},{"type":"text","text":": to inform a component that needs to use mono version of tokens"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"oudsOnColoredSurface"},{"type":"text","text":": to inform a component it is placed on colored surface even if the mono is off"}]}]}]},{"level":4,"type":"heading","text":"How to use","anchor":"How-to-use"},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["    \/\/ The folowing view has a colored background \"modeOnStatusPositiveEmphasized\" with","    \/\/ - a text with the color adapted according to the adjusted colorScheme      ","    \/\/ - a button that uses the mono version of tokens","","    \/\/ As view","    OUDSColoredSurface(color: theme.colorModes.modeOnStatusPositiveEmphasized) {","        VStack {","            Text(\"Status Positive Emphasized\")","            .oudsForegroundColor(theme.colors.colorContentDefault)","","            OUDSButton(text: \"Button\") {}","        }","    }","","    \/\/ As view modifier","","    VStack {","        Text(\"Status Positive Emphasized\")","        .oudsForegroundColor(theme.colors.colorContentDefault)","","        OUDSButton(text: \"Button\") {}","    }","    .oudsColoredSurface(theme.colorModes.modeOnStatusPositiveEmphasized)"]},{"level":5,"type":"heading","text":"Debuging contrast ratios","anchor":"Debuging-contrast-ratios"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Some countries set up new laws so as to force companies to have a better accessibility of their digital services.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"This is for example the case for France with the ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"https:\/\/accessibilite.numerique.gouv.fr\/","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":", also named “RGAA”.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The WCAG specifications, for AA level, defines a contrast ratio of 4.5:1 for textual elements (i.e. texts), and 3:1 for non-textual elements (i.e. link’s chevron)."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"However it is highly recommended for mobile devices to reach AAA level because of the screen sizes and luminosity issues, i.e. 7:1 for texts and 4.5:1 for non-textual elements."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Some components like ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSButton","isActive":true},{"text":" or ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSLink","isActive":true},{"text":" can be used on ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSColoredSurface","isActive":true},{"text":" ; thus in that case we can know the surface color for a given component on it, and compute the contrast ratio, and in the end display or not warnings.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"To do that, some steps must be followed in your component implementation:"}]},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Rise the flag to allow debugging (e.g. i #DEBUG mode)","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Get the environement variable defined by the colored surface containing the applied color"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"In the component implementation, add a line of code comparing the color to test and that surface"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Then keep an eye on your logs ; warnings will be added there if WCAG 2.1 3:1, 4.5:1 or 7:1 ratios are not reached, depending to the methods you call"}]}]}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["\/\/ Rise the flag","#if DEBUG","OUDSWCAG21Ratios.oudsDebugWCAG21Colors = true","#endif","","\/\/ Supposing we are in your component View \/ ViewModifer struct","","\/\/ Get the applied surface color","@Environment(\\.oudsSurfaceColor) var surfaceColor","","\/\/ In the function defining the color to apply, add the line below","\/\/ where colorTokenToApply is the color to apply from a theme:","","\/\/ Non-textual components, in AA","OUDSWCAG21Ratios.debugContrastRatio(colorToApply, surfaceColor, .nonTextual)","","\/\/ Textual components and AAA to check","OUDSWCAG21Ratios.debugContrastRatio(colorToApply, surfaceColor, .AAA)"]},{"type":"heading","text":"Divider","level":3,"anchor":"Divider"},{"type":"heading","text":"How it works","level":4,"anchor":"How-it-works"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"A divider is used to separate content elements in a view. Two kinds of divider are proposed:"}]},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"OUDSHorizontalDivider"},{"text":" To separate elements stacked vertivally (VStask).","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"code":"OUDSVerticalDivider","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" To separate elements stacked Horizontally (HStask).","type":"text"}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"A divider can be colored using color enumerated in the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"OUDSDividerColor"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]},{"type":"heading","text":"How to use","level":4,"anchor":"How-to-use"},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["\/\/ Add a vertical divider between items","HStack {","    Text(\"Hello wolrd!\")","    OUDSVerticalDivider(color: .brandPrimary)","    Text(\"Happy to see you\")","}","","\/\/ Add an horizontal divider between items","VStack {","    Text(\"Hello wolrd!\")","    OUDSHorizontalDivider(color: .brandPrimary)","    Text(\"Happy to see you\")","}"]}],"kind":"content"}],"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/oudscomponents\/layouts"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"metadata":{"modules":[{"name":"OUDSComponents"}],"role":"article","title":"Layouts","roleHeading":"Article"},"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"patch":0,"major":0},"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Some components can be used for "},{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"layouts"}]},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"references":{"doc://OUDSComponents/documentation/OUDSComponents":{"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The catalog of all components provided by OUDS. It contains also "},{"code":"View","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" extensions and "},{"code":"ViewModifiers","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" to apply tokens and styles on components and higher-level views."}],"url":"\/documentation\/oudscomponents","type":"topic","title":"OUDSComponents","kind":"symbol","role":"collection","identifier":"doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents"},"doc://OUDSComponents/documentation/OUDSComponents/OUDSColoredSurface":{"url":"\/documentation\/oudscomponents\/oudscoloredsurface","title":"OUDSColoredSurface","identifier":"doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSColoredSurface","role":"symbol","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Used to define if a content is used on a colored surface."}],"type":"topic","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"OUDSColoredSurface","kind":"identifier"}],"fragments":[{"text":"struct","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"OUDSColoredSurface","kind":"identifier"}],"kind":"symbol"},"https://accessibilite.numerique.gouv.fr/":{"type":"link","titleInlineContent":[{"text":"Référentiel Général d’Amélioration de l’Accessibilité","type":"text"}],"identifier":"https:\/\/accessibilite.numerique.gouv.fr\/","title":"Référentiel Général d’Amélioration de l’Accessibilité","url":"https:\/\/accessibilite.numerique.gouv.fr\/"},"doc://OUDSComponents/documentation/OUDSComponents/OUDSButton":{"fragments":[{"text":"struct","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"OUDSButton","kind":"identifier"}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSButton"},{"type":"text","text":" proposes layout with text only, icon only or text with icon."}],"kind":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSButton","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"OUDSButton","kind":"identifier"}],"title":"OUDSButton","role":"symbol","type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/oudscomponents\/oudsbutton"},"doc://OUDSComponents/documentation/OUDSComponents/OUDSLink":{"role":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSLink","type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/oudscomponents\/oudslink","kind":"symbol","navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"OUDSLink"}],"abstract":[{"text":"The ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSLink"},{"text":" proposes layout with text only or text with icon.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"It also proposes layout to navigate forward or backward. The link can be displayed in ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"small"},{"text":" or ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"default"},{"text":" size.","type":"text"}],"fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"struct"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"OUDSLink"}],"title":"OUDSLink"}}}